<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1498] RegexTransformer: sourceColName version not handling multiValued fields correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1498</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Versions in use/compared:&lt;br/&gt;
Solr 1.3&lt;br/&gt;
(Nightly 5th August)&lt;br/&gt;
Nightly 22nd September&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As RegexTransformer is not different between the two nightlies, the&lt;br/&gt;
issue probably appeared before.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ISSUE:&lt;br/&gt;
Using RegexTransformer with the &apos;sourceColName&apos; notation will not populate&lt;br/&gt;
multiValued (actually containing multiple values) fields with a list but&lt;br/&gt;
instead add only one value per document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The version with &apos;groupNames&apos; does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;worked for 1.3 (regression):&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;field column=&quot;participant&quot; sourceColName=&quot;person&quot; regex=&quot;(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;^\|&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;+)&amp;#124;.*&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;field column=&quot;role&quot; sourceColName=&quot;person&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
regex=&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;^\|&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ins&gt;&amp;#124;\d&lt;/ins&gt;,\d+,\d+,(.*)&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;works for nightly 22nd Sept:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;field column=&quot;person&quot; groupNames=&quot;participant,role&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
regex=&quot;(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;^\|&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ins&gt;)&amp;#124;\d&lt;/ins&gt;,\d+,\d+,(.*)&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Both fields are of type solr.StrField and multiValued.)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Comparing the source code of RegexTransformer 1.3 vs. 22nd Sept, I found:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for (Object result : results)&lt;br/&gt;
         row.put(col, result);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(lines 106-107 of transformRow() 22nd of Sept)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP, JDK 6, Tomcat 6&lt;br/&gt;
Linux (RedHat), JDK, Tomcat 5&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
